popt4jlib
Interface PoolableObjectIntf

All Known Implementing Classes:
DblArray1Vector, FNPTask
public interface PoolableObjectIntf

interface specifies the contract for objects that can participate in thread-local object pools.

Title: popt4jlib

Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

Copyright: Copyright (c) 2014-2015

Company:

Version:
1.0
Author:
Ioannis T. Christou

Method Summary
 PoolableObjectIntf cloneObject()
          create a new un-managed object of same type as this object, for use by other threads as well.
 boolean isManaged()
          returns true IFF this object is part of a particular thread-local object pool.
 void release()
          denote to the pool to which this object belongs that it is no longer needed and can be reclaimed and reused by the pool. if the object is not managed this is a no-op.
